comments: Reddish (NYK) takes a step into Hyland's (DEN) body as he is airborne, altering his driving shot attempt.
Green (DEN) and Randle (NYK) briefly engage and separate as Randle moves around on the perimeter.
Porter Jr. (DEN) legally contests Toppin's (NYK) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Green (DEN) firms up over his left leg into Quickley's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Green (DEN) initiates the contact by wrapping his arm around Randle's (NYK) waist, affecting his ability to rebound.
Quickley (NYK) is moving alongside Murray's (DEN) path with a rested forearm when marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Green (DEN) establishes himself in Quickley's (NYK) path and does not deliver contact.
After the drive, Sims (NYK) is drawn into the air on the pump fake toward Murray (DEN) and marginal contact occurs after Murray's pass.
Brunson (NYK) legally contests Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Murray (DEN) brushes Sims' (NYK) arm and marginal contact occurs as Sims is in pursuit of the rebound.
As Sims (NYK) slips, marginal contact occurs with Murray (DEN) in the backcourt.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) briefly places a hand on Brunson (NYK), causing marginal contact to occur near the perimeter and releases.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) reaches across Brunson's (NYK) front in order to get to the ball, delivering contact that affects Brunson's SQBR.
Quickley (NYK) is established in Murray's (DEN) path and absorbs the body contact during the drive.
Quickley (NYK) is moving alongside Murray's (DEN) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Quickley (NYK) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
